# List all posible options for that widget ( i.e. text, command, padding, etc ...)
configinfo

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////  Geometry Management  //////////////////////////////////////////////////
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

The "grid" command, where you can pass along the column and row you want each widget to go in,
how things are aligned within a grid, and so on. Grid is an example of a geometry manager
(of which there are several in Tk, grid being the most useful).
http://www.tkdocs.com/tutorial/concepts.html

